..TEXT:
The lands in Egypt and Syria which the Sultan now
rules.  For this use of |corregge~, see Ps. xcv (Vulg.), 10:
`^correxit~ orbem terrae.'  Two Babylons were distinguished in
the Middle Ages: `Babylonia antiqua a Nembroth gygante (Nimrod)
fundata' and `Babylonia altera, id est Memfis (i.e., Cairo)
super Nilum.'  Dante perhaps made the Sultan ruler of both.
See ^Romanic Review~, IV, 484.
