..TEXT:
`Who fought with love up to the end': the Old
French poet, Beno#it de Sainte More, in his ^Roman de Troie~,
developing an allusion in Dares's ^Excidium Trojae~, narrates
that Achilles, madly in love with Polyxena, was lured into an
ambush, where he perished.  See also Servius's Commentary on
^Aen.~, III, 322. -- |Combatteo~ = ^combatt@e.~
