..TEXT:
Gallehaut was the intermediary who brought
Lancelot and Guinevere together; Paolo and Francesca had no
such go-between -- the book was their Gallehaut, their guide to
love. Cf. d' Ovidio+3~, 527.  Gallehaut in the French
^Lancelot~ was a model prince and knight, type of the faithful
friend and discreet helper in love.  Dante was strongly
influenced by the beautiful romance, with its idea of courtly
love.
..AUTH:
..PUBL:
..EDTR:
..NOTE:
..DENT:
..BTXT:
..TCHR:
